# Lore Compliance — Canon Guardrails

Before writing unit names, tooltips, briefings, campaign copy, or faction UI
text, validate against the Acoustic Paradigm and locked canon
(`MASTER_LORE_BOOK.md`, `.claude/docs/lore-bible.md`). Prefer the `master-lore`
subagent for lore-facing artifacts.

## Acoustic Paradigm (required vocabulary)

- Every supernatural effect must name its **acoustic** cause: frequency,
  resonance, harmonic, waveform, attunement, detune.
- Forbidden gameplay vocabulary: magic, mana, spells, psionics, mysticism
  as power source.

## Hard lines

| Rule | Enforcement |
|---|---|
| Godhead | **Binitarian** (Father + Son) only — no Trinitarian language |
| Azazel | **Nephilim**, son of Gadreel — never a Watcher |
| Watchers | Knowledge/tech only (**Oiketerion Principle**) — no innate power |
| Palettes | Guardians teal-gold; Collective amber |

## Raphael / Liaigh — Tobit Protocol only

**WARN:** Raphael (player-facing cover name **"Liaigh"**) **cannot be a
standard combat unit**.

- Presence is invoked only as the late-game support power **Tobit Protocol**
  (wide-radius acoustic binding of supernatural enemies).
- Respect the Three Limitations (The Ban / Heavenly Liturgy windows /
  Name Consequence).
- Empyreal Register for Raphael dialogue when applicable (see lore bible).
- Do not place Raphael on build queues, infantry tabs, or as a selectable
  hero unit.

## Process

1. Draft copy → check hard lines above.
2. If unsure, consult `master-lore` before merging names/tooltips.
3. Never contradict LOCKED claims in the lore bible.
